KW  - Endogenous growth
KW  - Regional integration
KW  - Trade
KW  - Factor mobility
AB  - We address the effects of a step-wise enlargement of a common market from two to three countries by using a three-country endogenous growth model. We show that integration of a third, technologically lagging country via trade liberalization causes a reallocation of resources which stimulates overall growth. Liberalizing trade with the third country leads to income convergence between the two established countries. Furthermore, we look at the impact of a liberalization of factor markets.
ER  - 

